{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260950,"nonce":"uUtDv13rtMt1zeULp8h9ZsTr8k4=","title":"Deferred formal/theorem-shaped avenues from regulator-coupling programme","message":"Deferred. Not actionable now — captures six theorem-shaped questions from the decoupling-chain plan §4 so they are recoverable for a future theory phase. None of these are work items yet; they become relevant if/when the empirical programme (stages 0–9) establishes the existence and sign of the decoupling effect.\n\n**Avenue 1 — Existence of a decoupling separation principle.** Under what conditions on (A, B, B_w, Q, R, T) does the Riccati optimal K_t admit an exact decomposition u_t = u_ff(t) − K_local(t)·(x_t − x_nom(t)) with K_local(t) strictly less than K_t in a Loewner sense? Conjecture: holds whenever the LQ-game value function decomposes into a steering term and a fluctuation term. Reference template: Anderson \u0026 Moore separation theorem for LQG, generalised to LQ-games.\n\n**Avenue 2 — Capacity bound on linear-feedback realisability.** Define a \"regulator gap\" as inf_{u_ff} sup_t || K_t · x_nom(t) − u_ff(t) ||. For what plant + cost combinations is this gap small (regulators and trackers equivalent) vs large (only trackers can decouple)? Formalises Gemini's intuition.\n\n**Avenue 3 — Representation theorem for RNN policies as time-varying linear-plus-residual.** Given a GRU trained on a control task with bounded loss, does there exist a decomposition π_RNN(x, h, t) = u_ff_θ(t) + K_θ(t)·(x − x_nom(t)) + ε_θ(x, t, h) with ||ε|| small? The interesting question is whether stochastic gradient descent under the H∞ loss converges to the tracker form preferentially.\n\n**Avenue 4 — Equivalence of LinearDynamicsAdversary and the H∞ ε-game in a limit.** As inner-PGD steps → ∞ and η_max is appropriately scaled, does the constant-ΔA Frobenius-bounded adversary converge in distribution to the free-ε H∞ adversary on a class of trajectories? Conjecture: only in the small-η_max limit and only on trajectories passing through a generic state-space point.\n\n**Avenue 5 — No-free-lunch result for biomechanical decoupling.** Given a plant with antagonist-pair muscle dynamics and metabolic cost convex-quadratic in activation, is there a structural theorem that co-contraction-induced stiffness must couple with feedforward drive (whereas point-mass plants do not)? Formalises Codex's biology argument.\n\n**Avenue 6 — Information-theoretic bound on velocity inflation.** Under unpredictable disturbances of bounded entropy entering at the velocity channel, does there exist a lower bound v_peak ≥ v_LQR + f(I(disturbance), reach_geometry) for some monotonic f? A model-free version of the \"robust-must-be-faster\" claim.\n\n**When to revisit.** After stages 4–6 empirically confirm (or deny) the existence of the decoupling effect and its architecture-capacity dependence.","files":null}]}